<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-17E03B46-02EC-4F60-8364-45837BC8CE84" version="4" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-17E03B46-02EC-4F60-8364-45837BC8CE84" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> Advanced technical views</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-0D85DF78-34BB-4100-87FA-328B320B64CF" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="80*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Icons 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">overview 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-760EBA32-BEC6-45E3-A9E4-195F656A10A3" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A1447893-9D54-4CAF-8BBA-BA3496119689-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A1447893-9D54-4CAF-8BBA-BA3496119689-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The M&amp;C unit is used in the following situations: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">New media handling 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Improve or correct print quality 
</p></li></ol><p class="- topic/p ">In practice the M&amp;C-scanner could get polluted by ink-mist. This pollution leads to a decrease in brightness, which ultimately will lead to different kind of errors. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A decrease in performance can be seen in the media calibration step measurement of the "whiteness" of the media.(<xref href="http://localhost:20346/tsm?tsm=TSM000376EN.US" scope="external" format="html" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>216003 Execute selected printer calibrations</xref>) 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">This M&amp;C-Scanner performance graph displays the average scanner brightness in percentage, grouped by different media types. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The X-axis represents the time stamps, while the Y-axis shows the average brightness ranging from 40% to 100%. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Each dot on the graph corresponds to a single measurement for a specific medium on a given date. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The graph is useful for analyzing scanner performance and identifying potential calibration issues. 
</p><table id="GUID-FCC30A12-2087-42BC-BD29-DE5B540DD75F" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="3.72*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="1.29*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="1.00*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Schematic overview</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Schematic overview Observations</b> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Solution document</b> 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E5683332-F026-4844-8652-45ACD8395D3A" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-8600DB7D-833D-4FDD-9D3F-11427FA3D5D6-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8600DB7D-833D-4FDD-9D3F-11427FA3D5D6-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Whiteness of the paper is media dependent. A scanner brightness of more than 90% is considered a clean scanner. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> No cleaning of scanner required 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-88056327-4711-4808-8557-EC049E3F98FB" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-68D81CE5-6682-42E9-99A5-E9863EF02CAD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-68D81CE5-6682-42E9-99A5-E9863EF02CAD-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Whiteness of the paper is media dependent. A scanner brightness of less than 90% is considered a polluted scanner. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Cleaning of scanner required See: Clean the M&amp;C scanner 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></li></ul></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-4D3B79C1-BFF1-40C7-8205-16308D33D09F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-264CC96E-2E39-44AB-A51B-3D618218A32D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-264CC96E-2E39-44AB-A51B-3D618218A32D-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">This tile shows traffic lights for all known and detectable print quality issues per customer print. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The information on this page is based on the graphs provided in the "Nozzle Performance"and "Media step Accuracy"-tiles. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Based on specific scri[pting all deviations described in those graphas are analysed and classified. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Note that not all scripts are ready yet, so the number of columns will be increased over time. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-7DDD8A6F-AAA6-4BBB-884B-9E6C39B8CE0B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-441F698C-D68A-4474-ABBA-5F575CFD312B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-441F698C-D68A-4474-ABBA-5F575CFD312B-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Overview of engine usage related to media-types (Media category) and print modes in a selected time-period. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Data shown in chart and table-shape. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-6432B1A7-F4DA-4637-92C7-0764FBC34CD9" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F274C264-F2E5-43E1-ADE5-4E0B2E04703A-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F274C264-F2E5-43E1-ADE5-4E0B2E04703A-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Summary of the used media-types (profile-names) in a selected time-period. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Data shown in pareto-graph and in table-shape. 
